            <title>[CASSANDRA-12154] &quot;SELECT * FROM foo LIMIT ;&quot; does not error out</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12154</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We found out that &lt;tt&gt;SELECT * FROM foo LIMIT ;&lt;/tt&gt; is unanimously accepted and executed but it should not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have not dug deeper why that is possible (it&apos;s not a big issue IMO) but it is strange. Seems it doesn&apos;t parse &lt;tt&gt;LIMIT&lt;/tt&gt; as &lt;tt&gt;K_LIMIT&lt;/tt&gt; because otherwise it would require an int argument.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
